===Alternative forms===
* [[cæment]] {{qualifier|archaic}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|ciment|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|caementum||quarry stone; stone chips for making mortar|lang=la}}, from {{term|caedo||I cut, hew}}.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/səˈmɛnt/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/s@"mEnt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-cement.ogg|Audio}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} A [[powdered]] substance that develops strong [[adhesive]] properties when mixed with [[water]].
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} The [[paste]]-like substance resulting from mixing such a powder with water.
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} Any material with strong [[adhesive]] properties.
# {{context|figurative|lang=en}} Bond of union; that which unites firmly, as persons in friendship or in society.
#: ''the '''cement''' of our love''
# {{context|anatomy|lang=en}} The [[layer]] of [[bone]] investing the [[root]] and [[neck]] of a [[tooth]]; [[cementum]].

